raw_meta_yaml:
context:
  version: 8.4.0
  python_min: "3.9"

package:
  name: natsort
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/n/natsort/natsort-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 45312c4a0e5507593da193dedd04abb1469253b601ecaf63445ad80f0a1ea581

build:
  number: 1
  noarch: python
  script: python -m pip install . --no-deps -vv
  python:
    entry_points:
      - natsort = natsort.__main__:main

requirements:
  host:
    - python ${{ python_min }}
    - setuptools
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=${{ python_min }}

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - natsort
        - natsort.compat
      pip_check: true
      python_version: ${{ python_min }}
  - script:
      - natsort -h
    requirements:
      run:
        - python ${{ python_min }}

about:
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Sort lists naturally
  description: |
    natsort is a general utility for sorting lists naturally either as numbers
    or as versions.
  homepage: https://github.com/SethMMorton/natsort
  repository: https://github.com/SethMMorton/natsort
  documentation: http://natsort.readthedocs.io/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - holtgrewe
    - synapticarbors
